name: hdc_execution_proof
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: hdc_execution_proof

description: |
  HDC Execution Proof — Level 10A.10: Real Forward Pass with Measured Latencies.
  Closes the critical gap: executes actual vsa.zig operations on real text tokens
  and records nanosecond-precision timings per stage.

  === THE GAP THIS CLOSES ===
  v2.18-v2.25 specified 24 Level 10A specs across 8 architectural layers.
  NONE were validated with actual forward pass execution on real tokens.
  This spec bridges specification → empirical measurement.

  === EXECUTION PROOF PROTOCOL ===

  Phase 1: CORPUS PREPARATION (Zero-Dependency)
    Inline Shakespeare excerpt (1,024 chars):
      "To be, or not to be, that is the question:
       Whether 'tis nobler in the mind to suffer
       The slings and arrows of outrageous fortune..."
    Character-level tokenization: ~70 unique printable ASCII chars.
    Codebook: D=256, each char → randomHV(256, char_seed).
    Context window: 8 tokens. Sliding window → ~1016 (context, target) pairs.

  Phase 2: SINGLE FORWARD PASS (Instrumented)
    Given context = ["T", "o", " ", "b", "e", ",", " ", "o"]
    Expected target = "r"

    Step-by-step with nanosecond timing:

    1. ENCODE (expected: ~4 us total for 8 tokens)
       For each token t in context:
         token_hv = codebook.encode(t)  // lookup: ~500 ns
       Total: 8 * 500 ns = 4,000 ns

    2. POSITION ENCODING (expected: ~17 us total)
       For each position i in 0..8:
         pos_hv = vsa.permute(token_hv[i], i)  // 2,100 ns per permute
       Total: 8 * 2,100 ns = 16,800 ns

    3. ATTENTION (expected: ~343 us for H=3 heads)
       For each head h in 0..3:
         For each token i:
           Q[i] = vsa.bind(query_role[h], pos_hv[i])     // 2,073 ns
           K[i] = vsa.bind(key_role[h], pos_hv[i])       // 2,073 ns
           V[i] = vsa.bind(value_role[h], pos_hv[i])     // 2,073 ns
         For each query position i:
           For each key position j:
             score[j] = vsa.cosineSimilarity(Q[i], K[j])  // 190 ns
           Apply phi-rank softmax:
             sorted_indices = argsort(scores)
             weights[k] = phi^(-k/T) for rank k
             normalize weights
           attended = vsa.bundle2(V[top1], V[top2])        // 2,387 ns
           // For 3+ candidates: sequential bundle2
       Merge heads:
         merged = vsa.bundle3(head0_out, head1_out, head2_out)  // 2,387 ns
       Total attention: 3 * (8*3*2073 + 8*8*190 + 8*2387) + 2387
                      ≈ 3 * (49,752 + 12,160 + 19,096) + 2,387
                      = 3 * 81,008 + 2,387 = 245,411 ns ≈ 245 us

    4. FEED-FORWARD (expected: ~12 us)
       ff1_out = vsa.bind(merged, ff1_role)   // 2,073 ns
       ff1_act = ternary_relu(ff1_out)        // ~256 ns (256 trits)
       ff2_out = vsa.bind(ff1_act, ff2_role)  // 2,073 ns
       residual = vsa.bundle2(merged, ff2_out) // 2,387 ns
       Total: 6,789 ns ≈ 7 us

    5. DECODE (expected: ~13 us for vocab=70)
       For each char c in vocab:
         sim[c] = vsa.cosineSimilarity(output_hv, codebook.encode(c))  // 190 ns
       Total: 70 * 190 ns = 13,300 ns

    TOTAL FORWARD: ~4 + 17 + 245 + 7 + 13 = 286 us (predicted)
    Actual measured: recorded in ExecutionProof struct.

  Phase 3: VALIDATION
    Compare predicted vs actual latency per stage.
    Tolerance: 3x (measured within 3x of predicted is PASS).
    Log: Each stage name, predicted_ns, actual_ns, ratio, pass/fail.

  Phase 4: BATCH FORWARD (100 samples)
    Run 100 consecutive forward passes.
    Record min/max/avg/p50/p99 per stage.
    Compute throughput: samples/sec.

  Phase 5: CORRECTNESS CHECK
    After training (separate spec), forward should predict correctly
    for seen context windows. Pre-training: random prediction expected
    (1/70 baseline accuracy = 1.4%).

  === WHAT THIS PROVES ===
  1. The attention architecture (bind Q/K/V, cosine score, bundle V) EXECUTES.
  2. Measured latencies can be compared to predicted budgets.
  3. The forward pass produces a valid output HV that decodes to a character.
  4. Throughput is measurable and reproducible.

  Trinity Identity: phi^2 + 1/phi^2 = 3
  Sacred Formula: V = n * 3^k * pi^m * phi^p * e^q

types:
  StageLatency:
    fields:
      stage_name: String
      predicted_ns: usize
      actual_ns: usize
      ratio: Float
      passed: Bool

  ForwardProof:
    fields:
      input_text: String
      input_tokens: List<String>
      context_size: usize
      num_heads: usize
      dimension: usize
      vocab_size: usize
      stage_latencies: List<StageLatency>
      total_predicted_ns: usize
      total_actual_ns: usize
      output_hv_density: Float
      predicted_char: String
      predicted_confidence: Float
      all_stages_passed: Bool

  BatchProof:
    fields:
      num_samples: usize
      min_latency_ns: usize
      max_latency_ns: usize
      avg_latency_ns: usize
      p50_latency_ns: usize
      p99_latency_ns: usize
      throughput_samples_per_sec: Float
      total_time_ms: Float

  CorrectnessCheck:
    fields:
      total_predictions: usize
      correct_predictions: usize
      accuracy: Float
      baseline_accuracy: Float
      above_baseline: Bool

  ExecutionProof:
    fields:
      single_forward: ForwardProof
      batch_forward: BatchProof
      correctness: CorrectnessCheck
      timestamp: String
      zig_version: String
      platform: String

behaviors:
  - name: initProofEngine
    given: Dimension D=256, num_heads H=3, inline Shakespeare corpus
    when: Build codebook, generate role vectors, tokenize corpus, create samples
    then: Proof engine ready with real data loaded

  - name: executeOneForward
    given: 8-token context window from real corpus
    when: |
      Instrumented forward pass with nanosecond timing per stage:
      encode → permute(position) → bind(Q,K,V) per head → cosineSimilarity(Q,K)
      → phi-rank weights → bundle(V) → bundle3(heads) → bind(FFN) → decode
    then: Returns ForwardProof with actual ns per stage and predicted vs actual comparison

  - name: measureEncodeStage
    given: 8 tokens and codebook
    when: codebook.encode(token) for each, record total ns
    then: StageLatency for encode (predicted 4,000 ns)

  - name: measurePositionStage
    given: 8 encoded token HVs
    when: vsa.permute(token_hv, position) for each, record total ns
    then: StageLatency for position encoding (predicted 16,800 ns)

  - name: measureAttentionStage
    given: 8 positioned HVs, 3 head role sets (Q,K,V roles)
    when: |
      Per head: bind Q/K/V for 8 tokens, compute 8x8 cosine similarities,
      phi-rank softmax, bundle top-2 values. Merge 3 heads via bundle3.
    then: StageLatency for attention (predicted ~245,000 ns)

  - name: measureFFNStage
    given: Merged attention output HV
    when: bind(ff1) → ternary_relu → bind(ff2) → bundle2(residual)
    then: StageLatency for FFN (predicted ~7,000 ns)

  - name: measureDecodeStage
    given: Output HV and vocab codebook (70 chars)
    when: cosineSimilarity(output, codebook[c]) for all c, find argmax
    then: StageLatency for decode (predicted 13,300 ns) + predicted character

  - name: validateLatencies
    given: List of StageLatency entries
    when: Check each ratio (actual/predicted) is within 3x tolerance
    then: Returns pass/fail per stage and overall validation result

  - name: executeBatchForward
    given: 100 (context, target) samples from corpus
    when: Run executeOneForward 100 times, collect all latencies
    then: Returns BatchProof with min/max/avg/p50/p99 statistics

  - name: checkPreTrainingCorrectness
    given: 100 forward passes with predicted vs actual targets
    when: Count matches, compute accuracy
    then: CorrectnessCheck (expected ~1/70 = 1.4% before training)

  - name: assembleExecutionProof
    given: ForwardProof, BatchProof, CorrectnessCheck
    when: Bundle all results with platform metadata
    then: Complete ExecutionProof document

  - name: generateProofReport
    given: ExecutionProof
    when: Format as markdown with stage breakdown table, batch statistics, verdict
    then: Human-readable proof that forward pass executes on real tokens

  - name: compareToSpecBudget
    given: ExecutionProof and spec-predicted latency budget (389 us/sample)
    when: Compare total actual vs total predicted, compute ratio
    then: Returns whether implementation meets spec performance budget

test_cases:
  - name: forward_proof_executes
    description: Single forward pass completes and returns valid output
    expected: ForwardProof with all stages having actual_ns > 0

  - name: output_is_valid_char
    description: Decoded output is a character from the vocabulary
    expected: predicted_char is in vocab (printable ASCII)

  - name: latencies_within_budget
    description: Each stage within 3x of predicted latency
    expected: all_stages_passed = true

  - name: batch_throughput_positive
    description: 100-sample batch completes with measurable throughput
    expected: throughput_samples_per_sec > 0

  - name: pre_training_accuracy_baseline
    description: Untrained model accuracy near random baseline
    expected: accuracy approximately 1/vocab_size (1.4%)
